<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-22T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-22T21:00:00-05:00" n="724" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d724">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.86/10: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-23T09:00:00+07:00">October 23,
                                1943—9 a.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received October 23—7:14 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>2008. Department’s 1480, October 15. I took up this matter with Soong October
                        22. He stated that the arrangement outlined for the disposition of deserters
                        in question had been approved personally by the Generalissimo and he would
                        have to take the matter up with the General to see if another solution could
                        be found.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>